hands_on_practices.solution:
1. By applying the Robinson–Schensted insertion to $w=416253$ one finds the insertion tableau $P$ of shape $\lambda=(3,2,1)$.  
2. The hook lengths $h_{ij}$ for $\lambda=(3,2,1)$ are
   $$
   \begin{array}{ccc}
   h_{1,1}=5,&h_{1,2}=3,&h_{1,3}=1,\\
   h_{2,1}=3,&h_{2,2}=1,\\
   h_{3,1}=1.
   \end{array}
   $$
3. Hence 
   $$
   \prod_{(i,j)\in\lambda}h_{ij}
     =5\cdot3\cdot1\cdot3\cdot1\cdot1=45.
   $$
4. By the hook‐length formula,
   $$
   \dim V_{(3,2,1)}
     =\frac{6!}{\prod_{(i,j)\in\lambda}h_{ij}}
     =\frac{6!}{45}
     =\frac{720}{45}
     =16.
   $$
